Adapted component: the `build_pytest_summary` algorithm from the upstream
`src/cmds/python/pytest_cmd.rs` (pinned at commit
878af7de99e0ba71da2e8fd996f6b52a1836e06c), re-implemented here in
`src/minimizer/filters/python.rs` as the pytest state machine (`filter_pytest`,
`pytest_success`, `is_pytest_*`, `looks_like_pytest_summary_part`). It preserves
failures, errors, and the final summary line; strips header framing, progress
dots, and verbose `PASSED` rows; and falls through unchanged on unknown-state
lines (RTK's defensive default) so xdist `[gwN]` prefixes and custom reporters
never cause data loss.

